  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {"id": "show_summary"},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "import pandas as pd\n",
    "\n",
    "summary_path = os.path.join(calib_dir, 'summary_by_engine_energy.csv')\n",
    "if os.path.exists(summary_path):\n",
    "    df = pd.read_csv(summary_path)\n",
    "    print('Headline Energy Estimates (T4 + P100):')\n",
    "    print(df.to_string(index=False))\n",
    "else:\n",
    "    print('Summary CSV not found. Run the calibration step first.')"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {"id": "notes"},
   "source": [
    "## Notes\n",
    "\n",
    "- **Colab session timeout**: If your session disconnects, the experiment stops.\n",
    "  The runner saves progress to `_run_manifest.json` after each cell, so you can resume.\n",
    "- **Model cache**: The Qwen2.5-1.5B model is downloaded from HuggingFace (~3 GB).\n",
    "  Colab caches it for the session duration.\n",
    "- **Energy measurement**: Requires `pynvml` (included in requirements).\n",
    "  Works on any NVIDIA GPU with NVML support.\n",
    "- **Results**: All output goes to `results/t4_energy_calibration_*/`.\n",
    "  The calibration script requires the full controlled result CSVs (included in the package)."
   ]
  }
